name: Annie E. Darr v. The Pennsylvania Railroad Company, Appellant

opinions.text:
Opinion by
Mr. Justice Mitchell,
This case grew out of the same circumstances as Nye v. Penna. R. R. Co., supra, 184, opinion filed herewith, and for the reasons there assigned the judgment is reversed.
opinions.author: Mr. Justice Mitchell,

attorneys: L. W. Rail, of Rail $• Jordan, for appellant.
Jas. A. Stranahan and M. W. Jacobs, for appellee.
casebody.head_matter:
Annie E. Darr v. The Pennsylvania Railroad Company, Appellant.
Argued Jan. 1, 1896.
Appeal, No. 12, May T., 1896, by defendant, from judgment of C. P. Dauphin Co., Sept. T., 1895, No. 58, on verdict for plaintiff.
Before Ster'rett, C. J., Green, Williams, McCollum, Mitchell, Dean and Fell, JJ.
Reversed.
L. W. Rail, of Rail $• Jordan, for appellant.
Jas. A. Stranahan and M. W. Jacobs, for appellee.
October 5, 1896:
